 and support our student accordingly.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\n<B>EMPLOYER ASSESSMENT</B><BR><BR>\r\n\r\nYou are asked to complete the EMPLOYER ASSESSMENT (found under ASSESSMENT INFORMATION at the bottom of this page) for the student named at the top of this page.  The online report should be completed towards the end of the placement period and certainly before <B>31 Jul 07</B> to enable compilation of marks.  There is no need for E Mails or printed copies - completion of the report online and \'submitting it\' is sufficient.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\nThanks or your support.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\nR J Laird (Ron)<BR>\r\nIndustrial Placement Coordinator<BR>\r\nSchool of Electrical and Mechanical Engineering<BR>\r\nTel: 44 (0)28 9036 6264<BR>\r\nE Mail: rj.laird@ulster.ac.uk<BR>',60),(1,'StudentHomeRequired2007',1,NULL,'StudentHomeREQUIRED, SEME-2007','<h4>ANNOUNCEMENTS for SEME STUDENTS who REQUIRE PLACEMENT</h4>\r\n<CENTRE>(This announcement last update: Mon 27 Aug 07 14:50)</CENTRE><BR><BR>\r\n\r\n<B!
 >Placement Status</B><BR>\r\nAll students are required to advise R J L
aird of a placement offer when received.  Advise the company name, vacancy to be taken, start date and salary to R J Laird by E Mail or telephone, details below.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\n<B>Faculty of Computing and Engineering Policy on Industrial Placement</B><BR>\r\nAll students are asked to note the following policy:<BR>\r\nâ€˜It was AGREED that on courses where Placement was mandatory students would not be permitted to proceed to final year without having first completed Placement.â€™ <BR>\r\nThe Faculty of Computing and Engineering places no restrictions on the geographic location of any approved placement.<BR>\r\n<B>This means that enless a student is formally EXEMPT from placement (or where placement is voluntary) all students in good academic standing should be progressing to placement.  In the context of placement \'good academic standing\' means having passed all year 2 modules with the possible exception of any one module to be completed following the Sep 07 Board of Examin!
 ers, ie one module may be carried into placement.</B><BR><BR>\r\n\r\n<B>CV Completion</B><BR>\r\nYou must ensure that your CV is complete before you bid for any vacancy.  If any CV is found to be incomplete (yet designated COMPLETE) when used for a \'bid\', the \'bid\' will be removed.  Subsequent use of an incomplete CV will result in SUSPENSION from use of the OPUS system to obtain placement.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\n<B>General Company Search</B><BR>\r\nPlease use any of the following sites to search for any company:<BR><BR>\r\n\r\nwww.kompass.com  - for companies worldwide.<BR>\r\nwww.kellysearch.com<BR>\r\nwww.applegate.co.uk  - for companies in UK and RoI.<BR>\r\nwww.bionorthernireland.com - for biomedical companies.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\nIn either site search for locality or company activity; find company\'s web site; look for careers or training or jobs or recruitment; look for internship, placement, co-op or sponsorship.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\nR J Laird<BR>\r\nIndustrial Placement Coordinat!
 or<BR>\r\nSchool of Electrical and Mechanical Engineering<BR>\r\nTel: 
028 9036 6264<BR>\r\nE Mail: rj.laird@ulster.ac.uk<BR>\r\n___________________________________________________<BR>',61),(1,'StudentApplicationsViewIAESTE2008',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,66),(1,'StudentApplicationsViewIAESTE2008',2,NULL,'IAESTE 2008 Application','\r\n<B> A number of students have applied to IAESTE.  This scheme will give you valuable experience and we would encourage you to pursue this avenue in conjunction with a placement.   Most of the IAESTE opportunities are short term i.e. around three months and could possibly be fitted in before or after your placement.<B>',67),(1,'StudentHome2007IAESTE2008',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,68),(1,'StudentHome2007/2008',NULL,NULL,'IAESTE Applications 2008 ','<B> A number of students have applied to IAESTE.  This scheme will give you valuable experience and we would encourage you to pursue this avenue in conjunction with a placement.   Most of the IAESTE opportunities are short term i.e. around three months and could possibly be fitted in !
